        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 21 at 6:58PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 657 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Calera. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Alabaster, Calera, Montevallo, Columbiana, Jemison, Thorsby, Wilton,
Gap Of The Mountain, American Village, Maylene, Lay Lake Dam,
University Of Montevallo, Shelby County Airport, Lay Lake, Mitchell
Lake, Shelby, Minooka Park, Waxahatchee Creek, Highway 145 and CR 46,
and Camp Branch.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
